##Wang Yong, the express delivery boy who moved the whole net, also solved several difficult problems for the Hubei medical team

Micro-signal Xinminzhoukan

Function description, depth and angle —— this is what we can do.

For the "Red" Wang Yong does not care, as a bureau of the people, he can not stop.

By Wu Xue

Wang Yong, a delivery boy, became an internet celebrity overnight. After the report was published, Xinmin received thousands of messages from enthusiastic readers offering donations. At present, we have set up a special team to coordinate the donation of materials. As a matter of fact, Wang Yong doesn't care about the popularity, as a bureau organizer, he can not stop his steps.
On Feb. 2, Wang Yong posted a message on his friends'circle, saying, I have been able to hold it for so many days, but the concern of a nurse made me cry

At 6 a.m. on Feb. 16, in the heavy snow in Wuhan, Wang Yong simply padded his stomach, started his car parked outside and began the day's work. "It was snowing in Wuhan today and it was difficult to get a taxi. I sent a medical staff to work at 7 am, " Wang said. Since Didi, Qingju and mobike intervened, the medical staff was basically satisfied with their trip, no one would have bothered him if it wasn't for the extreme weather.
Green Tangerine Cycling Service Point at Kam Yin Tam Hospital, Wuhan

At 8:00 a.m. , Wang had to help a reader, Ms. Shi, 37, who has a special status, who turned to the weekly for help. She is a new coronary pneumonia patient, is also the first gold and silver pool hospital to donate plasma rehabilitation patients. February 9, just from a designated hospital in Wuhan recovered from the hospital. Ms Shi said her father, who also suffered from new pneumonia, had been told to go to the hospital on February 16 to collect his belongings as a relative.
On February 15, Ms. Shi was donating blood plasma at Wuhan Jinyintan Hospital

Ms Shi's home in Jiangan district Huaqiao community, the community can not send a car to pick up. When Wang Yong found out, he readily agreed to help. To reduce the risk of infection, Wang said he would not recommend a volunteer convoy to pick up Ms. Shi, who has recovered, but he could try to find a way to tow a Mandarin Orange Bicycle from near Jinyintan hospital. "When I pulled the bike over, it was actually out of service and I couldn't unlock it. I called Qingju bike and after the other party checked the Qr Code, it was quickly solved, " Wang told Xinmin Weekly when he learned about Ms. Shi's condition, she was so upset, she gave her an N95 mask and a bottle of alcohol.
Getting these two things done is only the beginning of Wang Yong's day at work. On February 15, Wang Yong purchased 200 wash and care products and distributed them at the front desks of the three hotels where the medical team from Wuhan was staying throughout the country. All of a sudden, they were distributed by seconds. Careful, he found that the quantity was far from enough. So on the 16th, he posted in the friend circle of the purchase information: toothbrush 500, toothpaste 200, shower gel, shampoo 200 bottles. Wang said weekly readers had donated 1,000 copies of each toiletry item since the report was published, but were on their way. Until then, he would make sure that each person got a tube of toothpaste, a bottle of soap, and a bottle of shampoo in two rooms.
Self-service collection point for front-desk toiletries at the Polar Sea World Hotel Vienna where medical staff are staying

On the same day, a reader named "Su Su" also asked for help from the weekly magazine. He saw Cheng Yahui, a junior high school student from the Shanghai Chi-yuan Wuhan medical team, posting a friend circle saying, "Countless Times, I raised my hand to help patients hang water, change medicine, and my shoulder was very painful. " The periarthritis of shoulder ointment is urgently needed. Want to ask Wang Yong to help, Wang Yong contact with the nurse, actually found that the shoulder Zhou Yan ointment is the common needs of the medical staff. "A lot of people do. Maybe they don't want to bother me. I bought 30 boxes and put them at the front desk. They can pick them up on their own. "
Su Su Su said that Cheng Yahui is very busy taking care of patients every day, and sometimes it takes two days to reply to wechat messages

Cheng Yahui hair friends said ointment is not enough

By lunchtime, Wang Yong was eating his lunch box, but his brain wasn't resting. In Wang Yong's dictation, after Kim Busan was shut down, it was mentioned that a local business in Wuhan, the Today convenience store, had solved the dining problem. The Today factory is located in an industrial park at Wuhu Farm in Huangpi District, Wuhan. Due to the severity of the epidemic in the area, the government has strictly controlled the entry and exit of people in the last two days, Wang told Xinmin Weekly, the park may well be at risk of closure.
"If the factory that provides 15,000 boxes a day closes, I'll have to find a way to fill the gap in advance, " Wang said as he ate at 12 p.m. Soon, Wang Yong had a preliminary idea, he decided to use instant noodles, eggs, sausages and other top consumer goods. "unlike cooked food, these items are not subject to time and transportation conditions, and there is no delivery lag. "
Lunch boxes from Today's convenience store

Wang Yong posted a friend's circle of friends asking for 70,000 copies of each soaking egg and ham sausage at cost price, while docking the Today convenience store and getting a detailed delivery order from each hospital. Next, Wang began arranging volunteer accountants to localize all the information based on the number of cars and the distribution area, and calculate how many cars each area would need, based on the standard of 300 copies delivered by one car. "In two hours, we found 20 cars, two vans, several sedans, and at 2:00 in the afternoon, I was able to get through the upstream supply and the delivery at the end. "
At this point, Wang Yong's heart was half-way down. At 2:30 p.m. , he began trying to contact the authorities in the factory's warehouse district for help. "They are quick to respond when they know what's going on with their meals, and they respond after 15 minutes of debriefing, " he said, adding that officials will coordinate immediately to ensure production at Today's convenience store factories, and that they will have to go through some formalities later, but it can be done at the same time as factory production.
The matter was settled, and in the evening, Wang Yong wrote excitedly in his circle of friends: I did a great job today. Wang told the Xinmin Weekly that his coordination and communication have been more successful since he became more influential, but that many odds and ends also take up a lot of energy, he said, still want to focus on the docking service of the aid-han medical team and the collection and distribution of emergency medical supplies.
Today's own fresh food factory provides including Bento, hot dry noodles, fried rice, sandwiches, rice balls and other products

Wang Yong's heart was completely free at last. Later, Xinmin Weekly contacted the head of Today's convenience store, who said there were still shortages of manpower and transport capacity after the government made every effort to ensure that the company would produce as planned. For example, some areas of the road closure, transport may not be timely. After many small areas in Wuhan are closed for management, there will be some difficulties for workers to go to work, and migrant workers can not return to the city. "In principle, 45 workers can guarantee basic production in hospitals, but to reach the expected 200,000 boxes per day, it would require at least 100 workers, but this is a skilled job and there are no temporary arrests. "
As a start-up, they, like Wang, are a match-maker because they have limited power to serve food to more than 60 hospitals in Wuhan, the head of the Today store said. Behind them, there are many caring enterprises involved. For example, the Today convenience store has donated 10.11 million yuan in donations and materials together with Taihe capital, Xinzhongli and other enterprises and caring people who do not want to be named. As of Feb. 16, vipshop had donated 4,058 servings of fresh food to Jinyintan Hospital, 547533 servings of fresh food and supplies to nearly 60 hospitals in Wuhan, and a total of 78,960 bottles of Jane Eyre Yogurt were donated by Pucheng dairy. "there is only so much we can do, " he said. "We can only do our best to give the front-line doctors a hot meal. "
Dairy products from Park Sung dairy

After Xinmin opened the channel of "donated materials" , the volunteer team of North American students and several domestic foundations also contacted us to offer help to Wuhan's first-line medical care. But they all face a common problem: logistics. According to Yang Fan (not his real name) , a volunteer with the new Sunshine Foundation in Beijing, since January 24, they have made 21 purchases at home and abroad, including overseas sources from South Africa, Japan and India, there are a large number of masks, protective clothing, disinfectant and medical equipment, connecting 103 hospitals in Hubei Province.
But the current logistics can only reach the warehouse in Wuhan, then down to the Huanggang, Xiaogan and other hospitals transport, it takes an hour or two by car, vehicles and drivers are too difficult to find. "when the truck arrived at Daokou in Wuhan, it needed a team from the city to meet it. At present, there are medical equipment and 84 disinfectant stuck at the Daokou. The Wuhan Logistics Association has only solved the problem of disinfection cabinet transportation,"Yang told the Xinmin Weekly.
Wang Yong, the delivery guy

On February 16, Zhang Fang, a staff member of the Charity Promotion and Social Work Office of the Wuhan Civil Affairs Bureau, saw the Xinmin report and contacted a reporter, saying that she could issue an entry and exit certificate in the name of a targeted donation to a hospital At the same time, she said, it is difficult to transport the contact in the field, but it can also help to coordinate.
As night falls on the Kong Hon Bridge in Wuhan, Wang Yong drives his car, which has been fighting with him for 25 days, through the snowy night, the phone keeps popping up with messages: "Wang Yong, the protective clothing has been sent to the hospital. " "Wang Yong, the book has contacted the supplier. " "Wang Yong, it's going to hail tomorrow. I'll be out of the car in the morning. " ... Back to the warehouse outside the Third Ring Road, Wang Yong stopped the car, did not have time to wash his face, and into tomorrow's preparation work.
"This time, I'm not alone, " Wang said as he slept peacefully in his bunk bed at the warehouse at 2 a.m
